				<div class="headline_area">
					<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://porkknifeandspoon.com/2011/03/29/pork-shoulder-marinating/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent link to pork shoulder marinating">pork shoulder marinating</a></h2>
					<p class="headline_meta">by <span class="author vcard fn">Shauna</span> on <abbr class="published" title="2011-03-29">March 29, 2011</abbr></p>
				</div>
				<div class="format_text entry-content">
<p><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-2304" title="pork-shoulder-marinating" src="http://porkknifeandspoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/pork-shoulder-marinating-199x300.jpg" alt="pork-shoulder-marinating" width="199" height="300" /></p>
<p>Coriander.</p>
<p>Cilantro.</p>
<p>Garlic.</p>
<p>Cumin.</p>
<p>Apply liberally. Add some olive oil, salt, pepper.</p>
<p>Marinate overnight.</p>
<p>Cook in the morning, low and slow, for as long as you can.</p>
<p>Eat.</p>
<p>Pork shoulder marinating promises pleasure later.</p>

