				<div class="headline_area">
					<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://porkknifeandspoon.com/2011/03/26/frittata-with-bacon/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent link to frittata with bacon">frittata with bacon</a></h2>
					<p class="headline_meta">by <span class="author vcard fn">Shauna</span> on <abbr class="published" title="2011-03-26">March 26, 2011</abbr></p>
				</div>
				<div class="format_text entry-content">
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2298" title="5566043612_ab52cc9883_z" src="http://porkknifeandspoon.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/5566043612_ab52cc9883_z.jpg" alt="5566043612_ab52cc9883_z" width="426" height="640" /></p>
<p>There are a hundred ways to make a frittata. It&#8217;s one of the easiest breakfast or dinner dishes you&#8217;ll ever find. Sauté up some vegetables (try potatoes or asparagus, or both), add some whisked eggs, some salt, a little cheese. Then throw it into the oven to cook fully. Eat.</p>
<p>Still, we hope you&#8217;ll listen to us when we say that the best way to begin a frittata is to fry up some bacon, set it aside, and throw the vegetables into the hot bacon grease.</p>
<p>Yum.</p>

